## 3. **Kafka Streams ↔ Redis Consistency (CRDT + Dual-Write)**

### **Problem**: Streams rebalance → Redis stale → saga inconsistency

### **Solution**: **CRDT Saga State + Exactly-Once Semantics**

```java
// SagaStateCRDT.java (Conflict-Free Replicated Data Type)
public class SagaStateCRDT {
    private final long clock;           // Lamport clock
    private final SagaStatus status;
    private final Map<String, Object> data;

    public static SagaStateCRDT merge(SagaStateCRDT a, SagaStateCRDT b) {
        return a.clock > b.clock ? a : b;  // Last-writer-wins
    }

    public SagaState toSagaState() { /* ... */ }
}
```

**Dual-Write Processor**:
```java
public class SagaStateDualWriter implements Processor<String, SagaStateCRDT> {
    private final KafkaProducer<String, String> redisSyncProducer;

    @Override
    public void process(String merchantId, SagaStateCRDT state) {
        // 1. Streams state store (durable)
        context.forward(merchantId, state);

        // 2. Redis sync topic (exactly-once)
        redisSyncProducer.send(new ProducerRecord<>(
            "redis-sync-saga-state",
            merchantId,
            JsonSerializer.serialize(state)
        ));

        // 3. Saga hydration always picks highest clock
    }
}
```

**Redis Consumer (Exactly-Once)**:
```java
@KafkaListener(
    topics = "redis-sync-saga-state",
    containerFactory = "exactlyOnceContainerFactory"
)
public void syncToRedis(String key, SagaStateCRDT state, Acknowledgment ack) {
    // CAS operation for consistency
    redis.opsForValue().setIfAbsent(key, JsonSerializer.serialize(state), 15, TimeSpan.MINUTES);
    ack.acknowledge();
}
```

