## 2. **At-Least-Once + Idempotency (No EOS Overhead)**

### **Idempotent Saga Coordinator**
```java
public class IdempotentSagaCoordinator {
    public SagaOutcome execute(SagaCommand cmd) {
        var clockKey = $"saga-clock:{cmd.merchantId}";
        var stateKey = $"saga-state:{cmd.merchantId}";

        // 1. Read current vector clock (CAS optimistic)
        var currentClock = redis.get(clockKey, MerchantVectorClock.class);
        var proposedClock = currentClock.increment("saga-coord");

        // 2. Idempotency check (cheap)
        if (cmd.commandId.equals(currentClock.lastCommandId)) {
            return SagaOutcome.Duplicate;
        }

        // 3. CAS update (vector dominates)
        var updated = redis.opsForValue()
            .setIfAbsent(stateKey, serializeSagaState(cmd), 15, MINUTES);

        if (updated && redis.opsForValue().setIfAbsent(clockKey, serialize(proposedClock))) {
            // Execute saga (now safe)
            return sagaEngine.execute(cmd);
        }

        // Retry or backoff (network partition)
        return SagaOutcome.Retry;
    }
}
```

